messages.name: AssetInfo

fields.name: asset_id
fields.description: This id value is unique at each domain.

fields.name: name
fields.description: Name of cloud resource from CSP like AWS, Azure, GCP

fields.name: ip_addresses
fields.description: IP addresses of cloud resource having public IP
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: provider
fields.description: Cloud Service provider like AWS, Azure, GCP

messages.name: AssetsInfo

methods.name: create
methods.description: Creates a new Asset. A Asset instance is created based on data including the `resource`'s attribute values. When creating, the classification information defined by AssetType is also needed. The created Asset has collection information which is the collection history for the `resource` by plugin.

methods.name: update
methods.description: Updates a specific Asset. You can make changes in Asset settings, except for the classification system of Asset and the information about the `resource` attribute value.

methods.name: delete
methods.description: Deletes a specific Asset. You must specify the `cloud_service_id` of the Asset to delete.

methods.name: get
methods.description: Gets a specific Asset. Prints detailed information about the Asset, including its state, classification information, and attribute values.

methods.name: list
methods.description: Gets a list of all Assets. You can use a query to get a filtered list of Assets.
